XP DEPOT - Privacy Policy
Effective Date: May 9, 2025

This Privacy Policy governs the collection, use, and sharing of personal information by XP DEPOT ("the Bot"), a Discord bot developed by Team XP Labs (Owner: .djzx, User ID: 523606077795860530). By using XP DEPOT, you agree to the terms of this Privacy Policy.

1. Information We Collect

To provide and improve the Bot's functionalities, we collect and process certain information when you interact with XP DEPOT. This includes:

ㆍUser Information:
    ㆍYour Discord User ID
    ㆍYour Discord username, global name, and server-specific nickname
ㆍServer Information:
    ㆍThe Discord Server ID and Server Name where the Bot is used
    ㆍChannel information related to Bot commands or features (e.g., level-up channel, game-winning channel)
ㆍUsage Data & Bot Interaction:
    ㆍContent of messages that trigger commands or contribute to XP gain (e.g., message content for message-based XP)
    ㆍReactions you add to messages (for reaction-based XP)
    ㆍYour activity in voice channels (join and leave times for voice-based XP)
    ㆍData related to your XP, level, and rank within servers
    ㆍInformation about your participation in games offered by the Bot (e.g., Blackjack, Button Search, Connect4, Hangman, Memory, Rock Paper Scissors, Texas Hold'em, Tic-Tac-Toe), including bets and outcomes.
    ㆍXP Boost status (multiplier and expiration)
    ㆍRole color emojis for display purposes
ㆍData Storage:
    ㆍThis information is stored in a MongoDB database hosted by us.

2. How We Use Your Information

We use the collected information for the following purposes:

ㆍTo Provide and Operate the Bot:
    ㆍTo enable the core XP and leveling system
    ㆍTo facilitate games and manage game-related data.
    ㆍTo manage the XP Shop and XP boosts
    ㆍTo display leaderboards and rank cards
ㆍTo Improve the Bot:
    ㆍTo understand usage patterns and identify areas for improvement.
    ㆍTo develop new features and functionalities.
ㆍTo Provide Support:
    ㆍTo respond to your requests and provide assistance through our support channels (e.g., our Discord Support Channel: https://discord.gg/QXU8x5DUBn).
ㆍTo Comply with Legal Obligations and Enforce Policies:
    ㆍTo enforce our Terms of Service and prevent abuse.
    ㆍTo comply with applicable laws and regulations, or respond to valid legal requests.

3. Sharing Your Information

We are committed to protecting your privacy.

    ㆍWe do not sell your personal information to third parties.
    ㆍYour information (such as username, XP, level) may be visible to other users within the Discord servers where XP DEPOT is active, particularly through features like leaderboards or rank cards.
    ㆍWe may disclose your information if required by law, such as in response to a subpoena, court order, or other governmental request.   
    ㆍBot administrators (Team XP Labs) may access data for the purposes of operating, maintaining, and improving the Bot, including using admin commands to manage user data as described in the Bot's features.

4. Data Retention

We retain your information for as long as necessary to provide XP DEPOT's services, or as long as your account is active on a server using the Bot. You can request the removal of your data associated with XP DEPOT by contacting us through our Support Server or via xplabs44@gmail.com. We will also delete data if required by law or if it is no longer needed for the purposes outlined in this policy.

5. Data Security

We take reasonable measures to protect your information from unauthorized access, alteration, disclosure, or destruction. Our data is stored in a MongoDB database, and we implement security practices to safeguard this data. However, no security system is impenetrable, and we cannot guarantee the absolute security of your information.   

6. Children's Privacy   

XP DEPOT is not intended for use by children under the age of 13 (or the relevant age of consent in your jurisdiction). We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under this age. If we become aware that a child under this age has provided us with personal information, we will take steps to delete such information.   

7. Changes to This Privacy Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any significant changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on our GitHub repository and/or through our Support Server. Your continued use of XP DEPOT after such changes will constitute your consent to the updated policy.   

8. Contact Us

If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy or our data practices, please contact us:   

    ㆍDiscord Support Channel: https://discord.gg/QXU8x5DUBn
    ㆍGitHub Repository: https://github.com/tiRo-DjzX/XP-DEPOT
    ㆍEmail: xplabs44@gmail.com
